<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="track-n">track <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /træk/    美 /træk/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>足迹；轨迹；车辙：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>follow sb’s tracks 
跟踪某人</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We saw wild animals tracks near the cave. 
在岩洞附近我们看到了野生动物的足迹。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>小路；小径：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It takes me only a few minutes to walk to school down a muddy track.
我只要沿着一条泥泞的小路步行几分钟就到学校了。</p><footer> 人教⑦ – 4</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>轨道；滑轨：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a single / double track 
单/双轨</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>跑道；径赛运动：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>track events 
径赛项目</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They ran five times round the track. 
他们绕跑道跑了五圈。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="keep-track-of">keep track of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>了解…的动态；与…保持联系：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They read the newspapers every day to keep track of current events. 
他们每天阅读报纸，以了解时事。</p></div>

<h3 id="lose-track-of">lose track of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>失去…的线索；与…失去联系；忘记：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The police have lost track of the criminals. 
警方已失去罪犯的线索。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I had so much fun that I lost track of time. 
我玩得很愉快，以至于都忘了时间。</p></div></div>